Mzuvukile Poni allegedly forced his way into the house of his wife's friend, locked the door and stabbed his wife 50 times. CAPE TOWN - The bail application of an alleged wife killer from Westlake Village is scheduled to be heard in the Wynberg Magistrates Court on Thursday.Mzuvukile Poni allegedly stabbed his spouse Vuyiseka to death in early January.Poni allegedly also chased his wife from her house following an argument.It s understood Vuyiseka ran to a friend s home where she is believed to have hidden in a bedroom.The accused allegedly forced his way into the house, locked the door and stabbed his spouse 50 times.She died on the scene.The couple had three children together.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)